PostHistory.xml:397:  <row Id="423" PostHistoryTypeId="2" PostId="183" RevisionGUID="fca7abbc-fe94-4f0c-a2f2-deafcf913597" CreationDate="2010-08-29T07:25:51.767" UserId="186" Text="How about this:&#xD;&#xA; &#xD;&#xA;[soft](http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/soft): &quot;having a bland or mellow rather than a sharp or acid taste&quot;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;[big-picture](http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/big+picture): &quot;the entire perspective on a situation or issue —used with the&quot;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;A soft-question is subjective and argumentative without a precise answer and can be a question **about** theoretical computer science rather than being a question in it. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Examples: &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;How would you teach X to undergrads? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Why computer scientists do X when Y happens? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Is theoretical computer science part of pure math? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Hong long do you think it will take to settle P vs NP?&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;A big-picture question is higher-level question, and although it can be subjective and argumentative it does not need to be, and is a question **in** theoretical computer science. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Examples: &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;What is the main idea behind Razborov-Rudich natural proofs? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;What are the obstacles to proving a super-polynomial lower-bound for SAT? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Where did the idea of Domain theory came from? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA; What are the main objects and constructions used in crypto? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Is there a program to settle Unique Games Conjecture? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Is polynomial time Turing computable the right definition for feasible computation? &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;&#xA;What evidence do we have for Church-Turing thesis?&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;(sorry for the bias in my examples.)" />
