PostHistory.xml:538:  <row Id="570" PostHistoryTypeId="2" PostId="234" RevisionGUID="812e20bf-b05a-4691-9a96-7aa18873c4ec" CreationDate="2010-09-03T19:42:07.137" UserId="74" Text="What is on-topic here?&#xD;&#xA;----------------------&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;As [our FAQ](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/faq) explains, we interpret &quot;Theoretical Computer Science&quot; broadly.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Here are some further clarifications regarding possible borderline cases:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA; - **Artificial intelligence**: theoretical aspects of artificial intelligence are on-topic; philosophical questions are probably off-topic – [more discussion](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/114/cstheory-vs-ai-stackexchange-site).&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Related discussion: [[1]](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/119/our-domain-scope-specifically-defined)" />
