PostHistory.xml:545:  <row Id="577" PostHistoryTypeId="5" PostId="234" RevisionGUID="7f8cb3eb-beb2-4c48-b4f5-928e9b4c3f9a" CreationDate="2010-09-03T19:59:38.837" UserId="74" Comment="added 144 characters in body; added 251 characters in body" Text="What is on-topic here?&#xD;&#xA;----------------------&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;As [our FAQ](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/faq) explains, we interpret &quot;Theoretical Computer Science&quot; broadly. Roughly speaking, the subareas of computer science that put **emphasis on mathematical technique and rigor** are on-topic.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Here are some further clarifications regarding possible borderline cases:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA; - **Pure math**: if the problem has some applications in theoretical computer science, it is welcome here – [more discussion](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/169/when-are-areas-of-pure-math-that-are-used-in-cs-considered-on-topic).&#xD;&#xA; - **Artificial intelligence**: theoretical aspects of artificial intelligence are on-topic; philosophical questions are probably off-topic – [more discussion](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/114/cstheory-vs-ai-stackexchange-site).&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Further discussion:&#xD;&#xA;[[1]](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/115/what-level-and-types-of-questions-are-appropriate-for-theoretical-computer-scienc)&#xD;&#xA;[[2]](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/119/our-domain-scope-specifically-defined)" />
PostHistory.xml:546:  <row Id="578" PostHistoryTypeId="5" PostId="228" RevisionGUID="17631653-1d76-4cba-bf1a-c448b3dcdee4" CreationDate="2010-09-03T20:13:40.533" UserId="74" Comment="added 1751 characters in body; added 120 characters in body" Text="What kinds of tags should I use?&#xD;&#xA;--------------------------------&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Each question should have at least one &quot;ArXiv tag&quot;, and any number of additional tags (there is a limitation of at most 5 tags per qeustion and at most 24 characters per tag). Try to re-use [existing tags](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/tags) whenever possible, but you are also welcome to propose new tags. See [this page](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/tags/synonyms) for our current list of tag synonyms.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;### ArXiv tags&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;[FIXME: add answer]&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Related discussion:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;1. [arXiv tags vs not?][1]&#xD;&#xA;2. [Proposal: Remove discipline prefix from the Arxiv-style tags][2]&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA; [1]: http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/41/arxiv-tags-vs-not)&#xD;&#xA; [2]: http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/118/proposal-remove-discipline-prefix-from-the-arxiv-style-tags&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;### [[soft-question]](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/tags/soft-question/info)&#xD;&#xA; &#xD;&#xA;A soft-question is subjective and argumentative without a precise answer and can be a question **about** theoretical computer science rather than being a question in it. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Examples:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;- How would you teach X to undergrads?&#xD;&#xA;- Why computer scientists do X when Y happens?&#xD;&#xA;- Is theoretical computer science part of pure math?&#xD;&#xA;- How long will it take to settle P vs NP in your opinion?&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;[More discussion](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/182/big-picture-vs-soft-question).&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;### [[big-picture]](http://cstheory.stackexchange.com/tags/big-picture/info)&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;A big-picture question is higher-level question, and although it can be subjective and argumentative it does not need to be, and is a question **in** theoretical computer science. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Examples:&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;- What is the main idea behind Razborov-Rudich natural proofs?&#xD;&#xA;- What are the obstacles to prove a super-polynomial lower-bound for SAT?&#xD;&#xA;- Where did the idea of Domain theory came from?&#xD;&#xA;- What are the main objects and constructions used in crypto?&#xD;&#xA;- Is there a program to settle Unique Games Conjecture?&#xD;&#xA;- Is polynomial time Turing computable the right definition for feasible computation?&#xD;&#xA;- What evidence do we have for Church-Turing thesis?&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;[More discussion](http://meta.cstheory.stackexchange.com/questions/182/big-picture-vs-soft-question)." />
