PostHistory.xml:2360:  <row Id="2523" PostHistoryTypeId="5" PostId="985" RevisionGUID="efc14320-32d0-4440-89c5-639a0e12a944" CreationDate="2011-03-04T17:25:45.607" UserId="109" Comment="revise text to be useful to someone arriving at question itself" Text="This is a list of questions at [CSTheory][1] focused on Theory B (Logic, Semantics, Automata  and Theory of Programming).&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA; * [Techniques for Reversing the Order of Quantiﬁers][2]&#xD;&#xA; * [Why do we need formal semantics for predicate logic?][3]&#xD;&#xA; * [What is the theoretical basis of imperative programming?][4]&#xD;&#xA; * [Shallow versus Deep Embeddings][5]&#xD;&#xA; * [Books on programming language semantics][6]&#xD;&#xA; * [Are there “small” machines which can efficiently match regular expressions?][7]&#xD;&#xA; * [What do we know about provably correct programs?][8]&#xD;&#xA; * [Axioms necessary for theoretical computer science][9]&#xD;&#xA; * [Which interesting theorems in TCS rely on the Axiom of Choice?][10]&#xD;&#xA; * [Solid applications of category theory in TCS?][11]&#xD;&#xA; * [Correspondence between complexity classes and logic][12]&#xD;&#xA; * [What's new in purely functional data structures since Okasaki?][13]&#xD;&#xA; * [Higher-order algorithms][14]&#xD;&#xA; * [Where and how did computers help prove a theorem?][15]&#xD;&#xA; * [What would it mean to disprove Church-Turing thesis?][16]&#xD;&#xA; * [What is the difference between proofs and programs (or between propositions and types)?][17]&#xD;&#xA; * [Relationship between contracts and dependent typing][18]&#xD;&#xA; * [Curry-Howard and programs from non-constructive proofs][19]&#xD;&#xA; * [What are practically computable properties of Labelled Transition Systems?][20]&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;This list is posted on the principle that one way to attract people is to highlight questions and answers related to their interests. This is a community wiki; please edit the list if notable new questions are posted.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;