Posts.xml:983:  <row Id="1033" PostTypeId="2" ParentId="1032" CreationDate="2011-03-01T01:43:53.160" Score="2" Body="&lt;p&gt;Since the site is designed as a Q&amp;amp;A site, I guess it is OK if the question is formulated that a clear single answer exists. As long as the question is in the scope of research-level theoretical computer science, it is appropriate to the site. &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;However, some of the questions are harder to be answered than others, and the correctness of a specific proof technique may be hard for one to response. Hope that you can find a proper way to state your question, and get good answers here!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;" OwnerUserId="1800" LastActivityDate="2011-03-01T01:43:53.160" CommentCount="0" />
